# Debug Root Cause

When debugging a failure, do not stop at a plausible hypothesis if direct evidence is available.

- If an error message says to check logs, Cloud Logging, Sentry, Datadog, CI output, browser console, or another external source, inspect that source before answering.
- Keep investigating until you can cite the exact failing command, exception, log line, status, or response that explains the failure.
- Final debugging answers must distinguish confirmed root cause from guesses and include the concrete evidence used.
- If the evidence source is unavailable or blocked, say exactly what blocked it and what command/tool should be run next.
